Prepare for Orientation
Make Sure Student Health Services Has ALL Immunization Records:
•	Check myUCF 
•	If you are on Hold, contact the Health Records Hotline at 407.823.3707 
•	You CANNOT register until you resolve ALL Holds and complete orientation 

Review Your Degree Requirements Before Attending Orientation:
•	The Undergraduate Catalog lists all majors and degree requirements 
•	Formulate questions once you have reviewed your degree requirements 

Print, Review, and Bring Academic Information to Orientation:
•	Bring (official or unofficial) transcripts from prior institutions 
•	Bring copies of dual enrollment or test credit 
•	Print UCF Degree Audit Found at: myUCF
Student Self Service > Student Center > Other Academic (Drop Down Box) 
•	Submit all final, official transcripts from high school and/or any other institutions attended to Undergraduate Admissions 

Check the Course Schedule Online:
•	Learn to navigate the system ahead of time 
•	The Course Schedule can be found online. 

Learn Your PID:
•	If you do not remember your PID, go online to myUCF 
•	Click on "What are my PID and NID?" link (located under the sign on box) 
•	If you have forgotten your password contact the Help Desk at 407.823.5117 

Sign Up for KnightsMail Account:
•	This is your official UCF account for ALL university correspondence 
•	Check KnightsMail for more information 

Placement Examination Information:
•	Students may need to complete a Math Placement Exam to be allowed to enroll in certain courses for the major 
•	If you have not already completed College Algebra, you will be required to take a Placement Exam 
•	For more information please visit Knight Source 

During Orientation
Be On Time:
•	Allow ample time to park and walk to the Student Union 
•	You MUST complete Check-In and have your immunization processed 

Dress Appropriately:
•	Comfortable shoes and umbrellas are recommended - You will be walking throughout campus 
•	Rooms on campus are well air-conditioned - be prepared for cool temperatures 

After Orientation
This Is Only the Beginning:
•	Be prepared to make individual appointments with an academic advisor after classes begin 
•	Review your schedule prior to the start of the semester 
•	Check fee invoice 
•	Get involved 
•	Be aware of all important dates and deadlines by reviewing the academic calendar

Remember 
Transcripts (Official Copies)
•	Transcripts (Official Copies) submit all college and/or university transcripts and test scores (through which you gain credit) to Undergraduate Admissions 
•	Submit high school transcripts to Undergraduate Admissions if you have completed the foreign language admissions requirement in high school 

Foreign Language Admissions Requirement
•	Complete two years of the same foreign language in high school OR 
•	Complete one year of college instruction in the same foreign language 

General Education Program/Associate of Arts (A.A.)
•	Students who transfer without an Associate of Arts (A.A.) earned at a Florida public institution may be subject to complete the UCF General Education Program requirement 
•	See an academic advisor on your campus prior to transferring to discuss these requirements 
•	Once at UCF, those students without an A.A. should meet with Transfer and Transition Services 

